Warner Bros. Fires Charlie Sheen, Weighs Future of TV Show

-- B y   R o n a l d   G r o v e r
-- 
2011-03-07T21:38:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/charlie-sheen-fired-by-warner-bros-fate-of-two-and-a-half-men-weighed.html
Warner Bros. Television said it has
terminated Charlie Sheen’s services on the “Two and a Half
Men” comedy, effective immediately.  The unit of  Time Warner Inc. (TWX)  is weighing the future of the
program, which it produces for  CBS Corp. (CBS) , according to Paul
McGuire, a Warner Bros. spokesman.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronald Grover in Los Angeles at 
 rgrover5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Golum at 
 rgolum@bloomberg.net  